---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import SheetEmbed from '../components/SheetEmbed.astro';

const fordSrc =
  "https://1drv.ms/x/c/1ab10ce1b91949c7/IQSfbkaNrLC9Q4gMSuvRxNr_AdZuC4Ru8pcFK8ov2DKisTw?em=2&AllowTyping=True&ActiveCell='Ford%20Financial%20Model%202022-2030'!B2&wdHideGridlines=True&wdHideHeaders=True&wdDownloadButton=True&wdInConfigurator=True&wdInConfigurator=True&edaebf=rslc0";
const dropboxSrc =
  "https://1drv.ms/x/c/1ab10ce1b91949c7/IQQrllCFDWAFR6IhtDzk43RIAVF-xxOswY-LxTKtQZmbXN8?em=2&AllowTyping=True&ActiveCell='Buyback'!B2&wdHideGridlines=True&wdHideHeaders=True&wdDownloadButton=True&wdInConfigurator=True&wdInConfigurator=True&edaebf=rslc0";

// "The fit, in her words" — each label is a generic finance competency; the
// load-bearing sentence under it is lifted/tightened from Denise's resume / report.
const fit = [
  {
    k: 'Budgets and forecasts',
    v: 'I direct a $5M+ portfolio: securing funding, tracking budgets, and forecasting needs proactively to attain operational savings.',
  },
  {
    k: 'Growth enablement',
    v: 'I planned for capital needs proactively, bringing the City on track to 7x its EV charging by 2029.',
  },
  {
    k: 'Financial modeling',
    v: 'Scenario, financial, and equity-valuation modeling: building assumptions and triangulating between bottoms-up analysis, street consensus, and research.',
  },
  {
    k: 'Preserve capital',
    v: 'I delivered $560K in building upgrades across 86% of City sites at zero capital cost through an incentive program, freeing cash for other investments.',
  },
  {
    k: 'Finance for non-experts',
    v: 'For stakeholders without a finance background, I anchor metrics to benchmarks: Ford’s margin against its competitors’ tells the real story.',
  },
  {
    k: 'Process improvement',
    v: 'I secured 100% executive buy-in on a new organization-wide vehicle procurement standard.',
  },
];
---

<Base title="Denise Lin: Corporate Finance" noindex={true}>
  <header class="hero wrap wrap--wide">
    <p class="eyebrow eyebrow--gold">Corporate Finance &middot; FP&amp;A</p>
    <h1 class="hero__name">Denise Lin</h1>
    <hr class="tick" />
    <p class="hero__lede">
      Eight years owning budgets and cost performance across complex,
      cross-functional programs. I direct a $5M+ portfolio at the City of
      Mountain View: securing funding, tracking budgets, and working with senior
      leadership to attain operational
      savings. Now a Berkeley Haas MBA, I&rsquo;m seeking a Finance Intern
      role at Harbinger because I&rsquo;m passionate about its mission. Let me
      show you how my financial planning and analysis skills can drive cost
      savings, growth, and financial stability.
    </p>
  </header>

  <!-- Portfolio first: two live models do the persuading. -->
  <section class="wrap wrap--wide portfolio" aria-labelledby="port-h">
    <p class="eyebrow eyebrow--gold">Portfolio</p>
    <h2 id="port-h" class="portfolio__h">Two models I built: live, and yours to poke at</h2>
    <p class="portfolio__intro">
      The clearest way I can show how I think about a forecast is to hand you the
      actual workbooks. These are two models I built, one for Ford Model Co. and
      one for Dropbox, for my Financial Information Analysis class. Both are
      interactive, with the dark blue font indicating hardcoded cells that change
      the model. Feel free to change assumptions and see how the model responds.
    </p>

    <div class="spotlight spotlight--hero">
      <div class="spotlight__copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Spotlight &middot; Ford Motor Co.</p>
        <h3 class="spotlight__h">A forecast is only as good as its assumptions</h3>
        <p>
          Automotive manufacturing is very expensive, and Cost of Goods Sold as a
          percentage of revenue is the critical assumption. Historical COGS / %
          Revenue has ranged from 86&ndash;88% in the past few years.
        </p>
        <blockquote class="pull">
          &ldquo;Consensus sat at 77% for the 2026 forecast, but this seemed way
          too optimistic for me; I selected 85% to consider the efforts
          management is making in increasing efficiencies, without falling too
          much outside of the demonstrated historical range.&rdquo;
        </blockquote>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat__pair">
            <span class="stat__num">~$14B</span>
            <span class="stat__lbl">My 2026 EBITDA, at 85% COGS</span>
          </div>
          <span class="stat__vs" aria-hidden="true">vs.</span>
          <div class="stat__pair stat__pair--muted">
            <span class="stat__num">$29B</span>
            <span class="stat__lbl">The street, at 77% COGS</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p>
          The street number would have landed at $29 billion, which is not
          really justifiable, as it is almost 3.5&times; the previous
          year&rsquo;s EBITDA. The active cell below holds that COGS assumption;
          change it and watch EBITDA move.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="spotlight__embed">
        <SheetEmbed
          hero={true}
          height={600}
          src={fordSrc}
          title="Ford Motor Co. financial forecast model, 2022–2030, built by Denise Lin"
          caption="Live model: Ford Motor Co. financial forecast, 2022–2030"
        />
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="aside">
      Finding the right inputs was its own challenge: different companies present
      financial statements differently. In Ford&rsquo;s case, multiple items were
      bundled in the SG&amp;A line of the income statement provided by Factset, so
      I downloaded Ford&rsquo;s 10-K to find the correct line items for the
      analysis.
    </p>

    <div class="spotlight">
      <div class="spotlight__copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Supporting model &middot; Dropbox</p>
        <h3 class="spotlight__h">Share buyback</h3>
        <p>
          A Dropbox buyback of 10% of shares outstanding, debt-financed at a 10%
          interest rate, lifts EPS only 1% while Debt/EBITDA jumps 16%. The
          result is increased liability and balance-sheet risk for a negligible
          per-share reward, making a debt-financed buyback unattractive at this
          cost of debt.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="spotlight__embed">
        <SheetEmbed
          height={520}
          src={dropboxSrc}
          title="Dropbox share-buyback EPS and leverage sensitivity model, built by Denise Lin"
          caption="Live model: Dropbox share-buyback sensitivity"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap wrap--wide section" aria-labelledby="fit-h">
    <h2 id="fit-h" class="section__h">The fit, in my words</h2>
    <dl class="fit">
      {
        fit.map((item) => (
          <div class="fit__row">
            <dt class="fit__k">{item.k}</dt>
            <dd class="fit__v">{item.v}</dd>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap section close" aria-labelledby="close-h">
    <h2 id="close-h" class="section__h">The lesson I&rsquo;ll carry</h2>
    <p class="close__line">
      Don&rsquo;t take research reports at face value: dig into the assumptions
      and see if you agree. And if your view differs from consensus, back it up
      with data and a hypothesis.
    </p>
  </section>

  <footer class="site-footer">
    <div class="wrap wrap--wide">
      <p class="contact">
        <a href="mailto:deniselihanlin@gmail.com">deniselihanlin@gmail.com</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true" class="dot">&middot;</span>
        <a
          href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/denise-lin"
          rel="me noopener"
          target="_blank">LinkedIn</a
        >
      </p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding-top: clamp(3.5rem, 10vw, 6.5rem);
    padding-bottom: clamp(0.25rem, 1.2vw, 0.6rem);
  }
  .hero__name {
    font-size: var(--step-3);
  }
  /* Wider, slightly smaller intro per feedback. */
  .hero__lede {
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1rem + 0.35vw, 1.22rem);
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 70ch;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .section {
    padding-block: clamp(1.8rem, 4.5vw, 2.8rem);
  }
  .section__h {
    font-size: var(--step-2);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  /* ---------- Portfolio ---------- */
  .portfolio {
    padding-block: clamp(0.75rem, 2vw, 1.25rem) clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
  }
  .portfolio__h {
    font-size: var(--step-2);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    max-width: none;
  }
  .portfolio__intro {
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 82ch;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  /* Narrative on top; the live embed spans the full card width below it
     so the spreadsheet has room to breathe. */
  .spotlight {
    padding: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 2.2rem);
    background: var(--paper-2);
    border-radius: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 1.6rem;
  }
  .spotlight--hero {
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-top: 3px solid var(--california-gold);
  }
  .spotlight__copy > :first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  .spotlight__copy p {
    max-width: 82ch;
  }
  .spotlight__h {
    font-size: var(--step-1);
    color: var(--berkeley-blue);
    margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  }
  .spotlight__embed {
    margin-top: 1.6rem;
  }

  .pull {
    margin: 1.3rem 0;
    padding: 0 0 0 1.2rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--berkeley-blue);
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: var(--step-1);
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--berkeley-blue);
    max-width: 68ch;
  }

  /* Pulled EBITDA stat — the accent moment. */
  .stat {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.8rem 1.4rem;
    margin: 1.4rem 0;
    padding: 1.1rem 1.3rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-radius: 8px;
    max-width: 46rem;
  }
  .stat__pair {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.2rem;
  }
  .stat__num {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: var(--step-2);
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--berkeley-blue);
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }
  .stat__pair--muted .stat__num {
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .stat__lbl {
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .stat__vs {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--gold-deep);
    font-size: var(--step-1);
  }

  /* Plain text (no card), full container width so it lines up with the
     spotlight cards above/below. */
  .aside {
    margin: 0 0 1.6rem;
    padding: 0 clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 2.2rem);
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    max-width: none;
  }

  /* ---------- The fit — two columns, condensed ---------- */
  .fit {
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1.2rem 2.4rem;
  }
  .fit__row {
    padding-left: 1rem;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--hairline);
  }
  .fit__row:nth-child(odd) {
    border-left-color: var(--california-gold);
  }
  .fit__k {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.09em;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--berkeley-blue);
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }
  .fit__v {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .fit {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .close__line {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: var(--step-1);
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--berkeley-blue);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }
</style>
